Cream together butter or margarine and sugar. Add salt, zest, juice, and food coloring. Mix until well blended. Add flour a half cup at a time, mixing well. Dough should ball up when finished. Shape into a cylinder about 2 1/2 inches in diameter. Chill for 4 hours. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Slice into 24 cookies and bake on cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes.